title: You Are Everything, But My Hero
body:
Markuson is a kid at school who’s constantly getting bullied, he’s got skills and brains, but there doesn’t seem a way out, no matter how hard he tries, even when he meets new friends that he looks up to with promising eyes.

Nerds, Jocks, Optimists, and Cool Teachers.

Your words burned off my lips as I whimpered softy. Only to be slapped in the face by the back of your hand. I fell to the ground in pain, the led gloves you wore scaring my face. You knelt down in…

summary: What if Jon, assuming he survives, after everything is said and done returns to the North to rebuild the wall and refound the...
body:
What if Jon, assuming he survives, after everything is said and done returns to the North to rebuild the wall and refound the Night’s Watch? If everything comes in cycles and the Night King/White Walkers are not completely destroyed and just return beyond the wall to wait again, then the wall would be needed.

It would be bittersweet for sure. It would also SUCK, but I’m speculating here.
